    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as our definitive anchor, boasting an elite 83.29 score. Facing RHP R. Nelson, **Henderson** benefits from a massive park factor boost (+16%) and a favorable wind-out environment, cementing his status as a must-start at SS. **Kyle Tucker** (72.71) and **Josh Lowe** (66.40) follow closely as high-ceiling options. **Lowe**, despite a lower lineup position, gains significant value from a +14% platoon edge and the wind, making him a sneaky play for stolen bases\u2014our most critical scarcity category. Similarly, **Luis Robert Jr.** remains a focal point; while the matchup against LHP Wrobleski is tough, his 61.22 score is propped up by a slow opposing delivery that screams stolen base potential, justifying his placement in the outfield despite the SP's low xERA.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved the MI slot, where **Jacob Wilson** (46.86) barely held off **Nasim Nunez** (39.49) for the starting nod. **Nunez** possesses elite sprint speed, but the optimizer signaled a hard bench due to his bottom-of-the-order assignment and a difficult matchup against Skenes. **Wilson** remains a marginal play at best; his score is hampered by a significant -19% SP skill penalty against Eovaldi, but he remains in the lineup to preserve our game cap efficiency. Elsewhere, **Nolan Schanuel** (61.68) and **Andy Pages** (63.77) round out the high-upside group, with both players benefiting from the +5% wind-out factor.\n\nRisk management remains paramount, specifically regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status of **Wilson**, **Polanco**, **Tucker**, **Robert Jr.**, and **Pages**. Should any of these players be moved to the bench or shifted significantly down the order, their efficiency scores will plummet. We are also monitoring the matchup for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who faces the formidable Skenes; while his platoon advantage keeps him in the starting lineup, the -19% SP skill penalty makes him a volatility candidate today. We remain cautious with **Liam Hicks** (54.36) and **Drake Baldwin** (55.41), as they represent the baseline of our production and will be the first to be evaluated if we need to optimize for pinch-hitting situations later in the week.",
